The police have detained a 14-year-old boy for allegedly sexually assaulting his seven-year-old neighbour on Friday. The crime came to light after the parents of the victim, who had gone out, returned home. According to the Peenya police, the girl stays with herparents and her grandmother. A resident of north Karnataka, the boy lives with his elder sister and her family. Following a complaint by the girlâ€™s mother, the police registered an FIR and detained the boy under the Juvenile Justice Act. The girl was sent for a medical examination. The accused will be handed over to the Child Welfare Committee for counselling, an officer said.